the simplest way i've ever seen to explain why division by zero is weird is to note that the answer to 'a divided by b' is 'the number which, when multiplied by b, equals a'
if b is zero, then you're looking for 'the number which, when multiplied by zero, equals a'
which, if a isn't also zero, is no such number
There's more red than dark, which by most accounts means lots of murderous intent or lots of hot lovin'
and if a IS zero, then it's EVERY number
either way, the answer isn't well defined
thhere are tricks like l'hospital, but that's why the operation doesn't make sense
it's also why saying the answer is infinity isn't really right either, because infinity times zero is *really* weird
